title: Blue Jays beat Rangers 6-3 to win wild Game 5
text: > Top News Blue Jays beat Rangers 6-3 to win wild Game 5 Toronto Blue Jays' Ezequiel Carrera, left, douses Jose Bautista with champagne in the clubhouse after winning Game 5 of baseball's American League Division Series against the Texas Rangers, Wednesday, Oct. 14, 2015, in Toronto. The Blue Jays clinched their first trip to the American League Championship Series since 1993, overcoming one of the most bizarre plays in playoff history by taking advantage of three Rangers errors for a 6-3 victory. (Frank Gunn/The Canadian Press via AP) MANDATORY CREDIT
